name: Programming Basics
description: Introduce fundamental programming concepts and algorithms.

name: Data Structures
description: Cover essential data structures like arrays, linked lists, trees, and graphs.

name: Algorithms
description: Explore algorithms for problem-solving and optimization.

name: Web Development
description: Focus on building web applications using frontend and backend technologies.

name: Database Management
description: Study database systems and SQL/NoSQL databases.

name: Object-Oriented Programming
description: Learn about the principles of object-oriented programming (OOP) and its implementation in various languages.

name: Software Engineering
description: Study software development methodologies, design patterns, and best practices.

name: Operating Systems
description: Explore the principles, components, and functions of operating systems.

name: Computer Networks
description: Study the architecture, protocols, and technologies used in computer networks.

name: Cybersecurity
description: Focus on protecting computer systems, networks, and data from cyber threats and attacks.

name: Physical Geography
description: Study Earth's natural features and processes, including landforms, climates, and ecosystems.

name: Human Geography
description: Examine human activities and their impact on the environment, including population, culture, and urbanization.

name: Cultural Geography
description: Explore the cultural aspects of geography, including language, religion, and customs.

name: Geographic Information Systems (GIS)
description: Learn about GIS technology for mapping, analyzing, and visualizing geographic data.

name: Ancient History
description: Study the history of ancient civilizations, including Mesopotamia, Egypt, Greece, and Rome.

name: Medieval History
description: Explore the Middle Ages, including feudalism, knights, and the Renaissance.

name: Modern History
description: Examine major events and developments from the early modern period to the present day.

name: Military History
description: Study the history of warfare, military strategy, and conflicts throughout history.

name: Olympic Sports
description: Cover sports featured in the Olympic Games, including athletics, swimming, and gymnastics.

name: Team Sports
description: Focus on team-based sports such as soccer, basketball, and volleyball.

name: Individual Sports
description: Cover individual sports like swimming, track and field, and tennis.

name: Extreme Sports
description: Explore extreme sports such as skydiving, bungee jumping, and snowboarding.

name: Winter Sports
description: Cover sports played in winter, including skiing, snowboarding, and ice hockey.

name: English Vocabulary
description: Focus on building vocabulary and language proficiency in English.

name: French Grammar
description: Study grammar rules and structures in the French language.

name: Spanish Conversation
description: Practice conversational skills and vocabulary in Spanish.

name: German Pronunciation
description: Improve pronunciation and speaking skills in the German language.

name: European History
description: Examine major events and developments in European history, including wars, revolutions, and cultural movements.

name: American History
description: Explore the history of the United States, including colonialism, independence, and modern democracy.

name: Asian History
description: Study the history of Asia, including ancient civilizations, empires, and modern developments.

name: African History
description: Examine the history of Africa, including ancient kingdoms, colonialism, and independence movements.

name: Latin American History
description: Explore the history of Latin America, including pre-Columbian civilizations, colonization, and contemporary issues.

name: Music Theory
description: Study musical notation, harmony, and composition.

name: Instrumental Techniques
description: Focus on playing techniques and performance skills for various musical instruments.

name: Music History
description: Explore the historical development of music, including composers, styles, and movements.

name: Music Production
description: Learn about recording, mixing, and mastering music.

name: Art History
description: Study the history of art, including major artists, movements, and styles.

name: Drawing Techniques
description: Learn drawing skills and techniques, including perspective, shading, and composition.

name: Painting Styles
description: Explore different painting styles and techniques, including oil, acrylic, and watercolor.

name: Sculpture
description: Study sculpting techniques and materials, including clay, stone, and metal.

name: Anatomy
description: Study the structure and function of the human body.

name: Physiology
description: Examine the functions and processes of living organisms.

name: Medical Terminology
description: Learn the language of medicine, including medical prefixes, suffixes, and root words.

name: Pharmacology
description: Study the effects and uses of drugs and medications.

name: Microeconomics
description: Explore economic principles and decision-making at the individual or firm level.

name: Macroeconomics
description: Study economic aggregates and phenomena at the national or global level.

name: International Economics
description: Examine economic interactions between countries, including trade, finance, and development.

name: Development Economics
description: Study economic issues related to growth, poverty, and inequality.

name: Environmental Policy
description: Examine policies and strategies for environmental protection and sustainability.

name: Ecology
description: Study the interactions between organisms and their environment.

name: Conservation Biology
description: Focus on preserving biodiversity and protecting natural habitats.

name: Renewable Energy
description: Explore sustainable energy sources and technologies.

name: Social Psychology
description: Study how social interactions and group dynamics influence behavior and attitudes.

name: Cognitive Psychology
description: Explore mental processes such as perception, memory, and reasoning.

name: Developmental Psychology
description: Examine human development across the lifespan, from infancy to old age.

name: Abnormal Psychology
description: Study psychological disorders and their causes, symptoms, and treatments.

name: Industrial-Organizational Psychology
description: Focus on applying psychological principles to the workplace, including employee behavior and organizational development.
